column5: We are heading to Whitefish Bay in two weeks. Would appreciate and info regarding muskie fishing so far this year. Thanks.

I saw on Just Fish Ontario site that the muskies were going good on the Woods north of Whitefish Bay up near Andrew Bay. There was a 51" caught out of Witch Bay Camp and numerous others this week. The big girls are starting to get real active. Seems 2 pm is hot. Sounds like it is going to get really good for awhile. People are seeing alot fish and they are chasing hard now. Good luck.
